<node CREATED="1566553055019" ID="ID_1747004651" MODIFIED="1566553055019" TEXT="The hierarchical database system structure was developed by IBM in early 1960s. While hierarchical structure is simple it is inflexible due to the parent-child one-to-many relationship. Hierarchical databases are widely used to build high performance and availability applications usually in banking and telecommunications industries." />
