<node CREATED="1566553055033" ID="ID_601619028" MODIFIED="1566553055033" TEXT="In this syntax: First specify the name of the view after the CREATE VIEW keywords. The schema_name is the name of the schema to which the view belongs.; Second specify a SELECT statement (select_statement) that defines the view after the AS keyword. The SELECT statement can refer to one or more tables.; If you don&#226;&#8364;&#8482;t explicitly specify a list of columns for the view SQL Server will use the " />
