<node CREATED="1566553055048" ID="ID_440390795" MODIFIED="1566553055048" TEXT="Domain integrity is the idea that every value in a column has a finite set of possible values. For example a column defined as INT NOT NULL can only have a valid 32 bit integer in it and a column defined as CHAR(1) NULL can be NULL or any valid single character." />
