<node CREATED="1566553055053" ID="ID_1120269083" MODIFIED="1566553055053" TEXT="Second normal form (2NF) is a normal form used in database normalization. 2NF was originally defined by E.F. Codd in 1971.. A relation is in the second normal form if it fulfills the following two requirements: (1) It is in first normal form (1NF) (2) It does not have any non-prime attribute that is functionally dependent on any proper subset of any candidate key of the relation." />
</node>
