<node CREATED="1566553055055" ID="ID_862464024" MODIFIED="1566553055055" TEXT="Boyce&#226;&#8364;&#8220;Codd normal form (or BCNF or 3.5NF) is a normal form used in database normalization. It is a slightly stronger version of the third normal form (3NF). BCNF was developed in 1975 by Raymond F. Boyce and Edgar F. Codd to address certain types of anomalies not dealt with by 3NF as originally defined." />
</node>
<node CREATED="1566553055055" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1941044140" LINK="https://www.studytonight.com/dbms/boyce-codd-normal-form.php" MODIFIED="1566553055055" TEXT="Boyce-Codd Normal Form (BCNF) - studytonight.com">
<node CREATED="1566553055055" ID="ID_141405490" MODIFIED="1566553055055" TEXT="Boyce-Codd Normal Form or BCNF is an extension to the third normal form and is also known as 3.5 Normal Form. Follow the video above for complete explanation of BCNF. Or if you want you can even skip the video and jump to the section below for the complete tutorial." />
