<node CREATED="1566553055097" ID="ID_283969560" MODIFIED="1566553055097" TEXT="Two-Phase commit and CAP. Two-Phase commit is CA (consistent and available). It does not handle network partition. When network partition happens then the request just block and wait for network to recover. This is the reason many people say relational database are CA. Drawback of Two-phase commit. 2PC is a blocking protocol." />
