<node CREATED="1566553055098" ID="ID_715872686" MODIFIED="1566553055098" TEXT="Concurrency control. Concurrency control is the process of managing simultaneous execution of transactions (such as queries updates inserts deletes and so on) in a multiprocessing database system without having them interfere with one another. This property of DBMS allows many transactions to access the same database at the same time without interfering with each other." />
</node>
<node CREATED="1566553055098" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_760114728" LINK="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/philbe/" MODIFIED="1566553055098" TEXT="Phil Bernstein at Microsoft Research">
<node CREATED="1566553055098" ID="ID_216864197" MODIFIED="1566553055098" TEXT="Currently I&#226;&#8364;&#8482;m working on a distributed systems programming framework called Orleans which was released as open source in January 2015 and is widely used inside and outside Microsoft. I gave a keynote about it at DISC 2014 . In the last few years I&#226;&#8364;&#8482;ve worked on projects to enrich Orleans to be an &#226;&#8364;&#339;actor-oriented database system&#226;&#8364;&#65533;." />
</node>
